Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (peeled and grated with a garlic press). Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(halved and diced) into small pieces. Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved) and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Chop the @baby plum tomatoes{125}(chopped in half) in half. Slice the @halloumi{250}(sliced widthways into 1cm thick slices). Place the halloumi into a small bowl of cold water and leave to soak.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a medium #saucepan{} on medium heat. When hot, add the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the @sun-dried tomato paste{1%tbsp}, garlic and @bulgur wheat{120%g}. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and boiling @water{240%ml} for the bulgur wheat (see ingredients for amount) into the same saucepan. Bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, put a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. When hot, add the peppers. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir in the tomatoes and cook until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Transfer the softened peppers and tomatoes to a small #bowl{} and wipe out the pan. Remove the halloumi slices from the cold water, pop them onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry. Pop the pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. When hot, lay the halloumi slices into the pan and fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} each side. Return the veggies to the pan for the final min to reheat.

Remove the pan from the heat, let it cool slightly. Spoon the @sweet chilli sauce{32%ml} onto the halloumi while still in the pan and allow to melt. Turn the halloumi a few times to glaze it. Fluff up the bulgur wheat with a #fork{}, mix in the parsley and divide between your plates. Top with the veggies and halloumi slices, drizzling over any sweet chilli sauce left in the pan.